animal.description: Meet Mimi a lovable, lighthearted and oh! sooo friendly! smooth coated female Chihuahua.  Born 07/11/2010; she weighs in at a delicate eight pounds.  Her beautiful solid cream coat requires only occasional brushing and grooming.  Mimi came to us from The Anti-Cruelty Society on 08/19/2019.  Their medical staff deemed her unadoptable due to a confluence of medical issues and recommended she be turned over to a rescue group.  They reached out to several Chihuahua specific and mixed breed organizations but no one wanted her.  We care about little loving pets and even though Mimi isn’t a Shih Tzu we agreed to give her a chance.   Mimi is housetrained but will need help adjusting to your household and schedule.  A spirited bundle of love and kisses; shy at first but when she warms up she is fun loving and playful.  Quiet (not the least bit barky as some Chihuahuas can be!!).  Well-mannered and self-reliant, she will entertain herself and can be trusted to behave when home alone. One look into those big brown trusting eyes with just a hint of mischief hidden in them and your heart will melt.  Mimi gets alone just fine with all the small dogs here at the Safehouse.  Her experience with cats is unknown.  Much too tiny and delicate for a home with children, Mimi is nicely suited to singles and seniors; she fits easily on a lap.  A nice match for apartment dwellers because she tires out rather easily with indoor playtimes and walks.  Mimi requires extensive reconstructive surgery to her left rear leg but, due to her severe heart murmur (Grade 5/6) she must first be evaluated by a veterinary cardiologist to determine her surgical risk.  Unfortunately the Safehouse does not have the resources available to implement these recommended medical procedures at this time.  Mimi is being given the best medical care possible, the attention of a dedicated caretaker and the comfort and care she needs and deserves to live as full a life as possible in a loving environment.  Mimi is spayed, microchipped, current on all vaccines, heartworm and flea/tick preventative; she has had a complete physical.  Her adoption fee is $300.

He absolutely LOVES to play.  Since Oscar and Jasper have been together for all of Jasper's life, these two will only be adopted as a bonded pair.    

A fenced-in yard is required.

animal.description:
Oscar is between 4 to  6 years old and weighs around 10 pounds.  He was removed from a "cruelty situation" and is now in rescue.  He was a little unsure at first, but he's doing remarkably well now that he's in a safe environment.  He's a very loving little dog and warms up to you very quickly.  He chases cats, so he needs to be in a cat-free home.  He loves to play fetch and likes to be in your lap as much as possible.  Oscar is really an endearing little fella.  Oscar is Jasper's father, and since they have been together since Jasper was born, they will only be adopted as a bonded pair.  

A fenced-in yard is required.  

Please go to our website at www.dachshundrescueofohio.org to fill out an application.  The application can now be completed online through the site and is automatically emailed to us.

animal.description:
Shadow is a 8 year old female Lab Mix. She is a little shy at first but once she gets to know you she loves being by your side. Shadow thinks she is a lap dog and enjoys a good belly rub. She walks well on a leash and will protect you from pesky squirrels. Shadow may be a little ""up there"" in age but she is still active and will goof around accordingly. She only likes to hang with fellow ladies and loves hiking and shredded cheese! When Shadow came to us (2 and a half yrs. ago) she had already been microchipped. She needs female companions with plenty of space from the neighbors. Shadow needs to be the only pet in the home. She is spayed, heartworm negative, and up to date on vaccinations. She weighs about 35lbs. Intake date 8/8/2016All Dog Adoption Fee's are $150 Cats are $75
Includes initial Vaccinations, De-Worming, Flea Meds, Heartworm Testing, & Spay/Neuter 

Adoption Application - http://vwchs.org

Big, playful, LOVES to play with other dogs! Clifford needs a home with a person familiar to working with large breed dogs and won't be intimidated by his size. He can be a bit pushy in his communication with humans, but only when that behavior works! Strong leadership with consistent instruction will be necessary for Clifford to settle in with his new family and find his place in his ""pack"". With instruction and clearly set boundaries, Clifford will thrive in his new home! Check in with a member of our staff for more information about Clifford and his training needs and whether he'd be a good fit for your household.For additional information regarding this pet please contact Utah Animal Adoption Center at (801) 355-PETS (7387).

Our shelter is located at 1955 N. Redwood Road in Salt Lake City. 

Open hours to the public are Tuesday - Saturday, 11 AM - 6 PM. Please note that we stop showing animals at 5 PM.

animal.description:
Well hi there! I'm Gypsy the Princess. That's what my foster momma calls me because I always find the most comfortable places to sleep. Blankets, piles of clothes, stuffed animals, couch bed or chair, it doesn't matter; I'm not picky! One thing I'm not crazy about is my crate but I am working on it. I just need someone to help me see that it is a safe place to hang out. 
 
Going for walks is pretty fun! Everyone I meet tells me how pretty I am! There is this thing called a ""cat"" in my foster home and he doesn't seem to like me very well. He runs away from me and I think it's a game so I chase him! Not sure what I would do if I caught him though. My foster momma has learned that I would do best in a home without other dogs. I just don't seem to appreciate their company. I would love all the attention to be on me anyway! 

Getting some snuggles from my humans is one of my favorite things! I love to sit by them on the couch and soak up all the attention. I share my home with a human boy and I really enjoy being near him. We have fun together! My foster mom says I am a very easy going, relaxed lady. I kinda just go with the flow and take it all in. I really love to please my people so I try very hard to always be well behaved. 

I can't wait to meet my new family. Hopefully they have a comfy couch for me to curl up on! 

REQUIRED TRAINING:
Gypsy's adopter will be required to purchase training sessions and work closely with our trainers so that Gypsy and her family will have the tools they need to help her with challenges she faces. All of the training information will be given to the adopter during the adoption process. 

------------------------------------------


All our Warrior Dogs will have all age appropriate medical care and vaccines, a microchip, and spay/neuter before adoption unless age is a factor with a puppy younger than 6-12 months at the time of adoption. If that is the case, the spay/neuter will be covered in the adoption fee and the owner will be responsible to have the procedure completed at a Warrior Dog Rescue Veterinarian at the appropriate time.

Please note that the majority of our dogs in rescue are from shelters where they have been found as strays or abandoned. Their breed description is based on our very best educated guess based on physical characteristics and their dispositions. If they came to our rescue as an owner surrender, the breed description will be listed as provided by the previous owner.

Adoption Fee - $350.00
Training Discount - $50
Adoption Fee after Training - $300

To apply for this pup, please submit an Adoption Application at http://warriordogrescue.com/adopt/adoption-application/

animal.breeds_label: American Staffordshire Terrier & Labrador Retriever Mix
animal.description:
My name's Matilda, and I'm a hoot! I am a 8.5 y/o, 65 lbs, Staffy/Lab mix girl. My Adoption fee is only $50.00 to a suitable family, background screening will be done to make sure I go to an honest, safe home!

Let me tell you, I am quite a diva! Although, I'm over 8 y/o and have had a tough life, I am still a confident, playful girl, who also loves cozy nights on the couch cuddling with my foster family. They say I am a great dog and I love to cuddle. You do need to give me a lil time to warm up to you and get to know my personality. I am a quirky, but adorable girl. I still have a ton of spunk in me!

I do well in my fenced yard foster home, which is great bc there are not any other dogs bordering the yards. I can get feisty with other dogs, so please, I need a pet free home. I do need a fenced yard. If the fence is see through, and there are other animals on the other side, I will not do well with them. So, privacy, or no other animals bordering is ideal. That is what I have in my current foster home and I do so well there. I LOVE playing in my backyard!! I LOVE sprinklers and playing in the kiddie pool, splashing in the water, jumping into raked leaves, and romping through the snow. I am a such a happy, free-spirit!

I adore my humans! Being an older gal, I am a little hard of hearing, but not too bad. I may have a little cataracts, but all pretty expected with age. For that reason, I can startle easily sometimes, so it's best that there be no children in my home. I'm a loving girl, but can be a lil snappy at times if I'm made to feel uncomfortable. My foster family have no issues with me, bc they did an amazing job going slow with me in the beginning. I am joined at their hip now! I trust them and love laying on them, sometimes I think I'm a lap dog! I get to sleep in their bed and love snuggling in the blankets! My foster family are such gentle, easy going human beings. They never make me feel uncomfortable, so we are having a great time together! 

I am looking for a perfect furever home where I can live out my golden years in peace, love, and comfort! Once again, I am still quite an active girl, and you'd never know I am 8.5 y/o, though. I have been through some stuff in life. I'm Almost Home's longest resident (4.5 years in the rescue, and have had 3 foster homes in that time).

All dogs matter, even older gals like me! A senior dog will bless you in so many special ways. Won't you open your heart to me and give me a chance? I will keep you entertained all year long!

If you feel a connection with me and want to give me my furever home, please complete an online application at: https://us01.sheltermanager.com/service?account=ah0334&method=online_form_html&formid=5

Located near West Bloomfield, Michigan!
Www.almosthomeanimals.orgTo complete an adoption application, go to: http://almosthomeanimals.org/applications/adoption/

animal.description: Sampson is loyal and protective of the people he bonds with so he needs an experienced dog owner. He was found roaming the streets of the Red Lands where he followed people walking to their cars and would try to jump in for safety. Sampson walks great on a leash and listens to commands as he knows sit, wait, and even roll over. Sampson needs time to warm up to people, and is people selective, but once he trusts you, he is wonderful companion. Sampson loves to play with squeaky toys and will toss a ball back to you. He would do best in a home by himself. We ask that anyone interested in Sampson, come and spend time with him to gain his trust. To meet Sampson, please fill out an application at www.abandonedpetrescue.orgTo meet this adoptable pet, please fill out an adoption application at www.abandonedpetrescue.org and a team member will contact you to schedule an appointment.

animal.description:
Friends, meet Vinny. He was the longest resident at the @castaicanimalslaco when we were there to rescue a dog. One of the volunteers stopped us while we were on a live video and getting ready to leave. She mentioned they had a dog there who was on the euth list and really needed out. We were told he had come in with his dog friend but he had been adopted. When we go to shelters we don't just choose the most adoptable little guys. Those will make it out. We get the guys who need a little extra help. Luckily at the ranch we have the resources to be able to help dogs like Vinny. He's working through some anxiety and uncertainty around other dogs. He's already made best bud with another adoptable dog we have named Doug and they're doing great together. Vinny comes with a free training session with Angela before he's adopted. We can not wait to see a happy ending for Vinny. He's such a sweet deserving little man.

https://www.marleysmutts.org/vinny-2/ If you are interested in adopting a Marley's Mutts please fill out an application at http://marleysmutts.org/adoptionprocess/

animal.description:
Hi, I'm Mike!

I am a 44 pound deep brindle hound dog. My people here at ARNO think I'm really handsome with my shiny, smooth, stunning coat that the pictures just can't capture. I am good with cats, dogs, but I do not prefer to be in a home with children. I'm a low-key kind of guy waiting for my low-key kind of person!

In order to meet me, you must make an appointment by emailing training@animalrescueneworleans.org.

My adoption fee is $200. This includes a spay/neuter, up-to-date vaccines, deworming, a microchip, a heartworm test, and, if needed, heartworm treatment.

________________________________________________

For all animals that have not been spayed or neutered a $100 deposit will be required in addition to the adoption fee. The deposit is refundable upon completion of the spay / neuter surgery.

For more information email: adopt@animalrescueneworleans.org.

To complete an application, please visit: https://animalrescueneworleans.org/adoptfoster/.

Please visit our facebook for more information about adoption specials, and adoption events. Events are a great way to meet multiple animals at a time!

Hey I'm Zeke!

I'm a big boy with very little maintenance. Can you believe the irony? I'm a 65 pound, 8 years old hound and pitbull mix doggy. I am a little shy and timid to start but warm up quickly and love all people. Walks aren't really my thing, but snacks and bad reality TV are. I am extremely low maintenance, 100% housebroken and have the most gentle disposition. I am disinterested in other animals when on a walk but prefer to be the only animal in the home (mostly because I don't agree with ARNO's assessment that I am, in fact, a dog). I would rather not be inside when there is a loud and crowded party. I'll be chilling out back until things die down. I need a nice yard with some shade to chill when it's nice out, a spot on the sofa to watch my pictures, and a few walks a week to get some sniffs in. I tried to swim once and sunk like a bag of rocks, so I'll never try that again! If you're a couch potato like me and need a best friend who thinks the world of you, then I'm your guy. Have you seen my adorable face? I love posing for pics. Let's take a selfie together!

My adoption fee is $200. This includes a spay/neuter, up-to-date vaccines, deworming, a microchip, a heartworm test, and, if needed, heartworm treatment.

________________________________________________

For all animals that have not been spayed or neutered a $100 deposit will be required in addition to the adoption fee. The deposit is refundable upon completion of the spay / neuter surgery.

For more information email: adopt@animalrescueneworleans.org.

To complete an application, please visit: https://animalrescueneworleans.org/adoptfoster/.

Please visit our facebook for more information about adoption specials, and adoption events. Events are a great way to meet multiple animals at a time!

animal.description:
Hello!

I am Eli. I am a senior chihuahua and pit bull terrier mix. I need your help: I am a bit shy with people, but if you have the patience, I warm up and become one of the quirkiest and funniest dogs you've ever met. I even like other dogs if you already have any in your home with you! I just don't prefer cats or children since I get nervous. I really, really need my own pack of people and/or people and dogs to make me feel safe and happy. I have been at ARNO for almost eight years. They are wonderful people who I have gotten to know so well. I love them so much that when they teach me a new trick, I want to impress them so I learn fast especially to get treats! Walking and running on leash are my specialty and so is basking in the sun! I just need an adult-only home, and someone who is experienced, patient and willing to help me build up my confidence so I'm a little less unsure about the world around me. I feel so much better when people understand me and see I am a loyal and laid back guy with a safe environment you've provided for me.

animal.description:
Hello my name is Scooter. I love to snuggle, car rides, walks, and playing tug of war. I love to
explore and will need a fenced yard to run in. Did I mention I am a hunter of birds and rodents?
I love hanging out with my people and I think I should get to go everywhere with them. I am cool
hanging out in my crate with something to do if I absolutely can't go with my people. I will sleep
in my crate if I must, but I would prefer to sleep right next to my human. Oh, my favorite job is
protecting house. My foster mom says I am like a gargoyle that way. I need to meet new people
on leash with a muzzle until I figure out strangers are not all bad, which may take some time. I
may need to meet the same person multiple times that way. I need to be on leash in the front
yard as well because of my protective tendencies. I am house broken and love the doggie door.
I don't like loud noises and I need to be crated when you vacuum or mow the lawn. I hate the
noise those devices make so much I try to kill the evil creature making it. I am good with small
dogs, but not dogs bigger than me. I like my voice, so shared walls are probably not going to be
for me. My ideal home would be someone familiar with strong-willed, stubborn terriers, and
willing to be the alpha. Kids are probably not a good idea unless they are older and are familiar
with how to handle me. My new family must be someone committed to me for the long haul,
willing to mitigate my territorial tendencies, and challenge me mentally and keep me active. If
that sounds like you fill out an application and have a chat with my foster mom.

Dogs are not placed on a first-come, first-served basis. We strive to find the perfect home for each animal. Applications may take up to 48 hours to process. 

All CAWS animals are fixed, microchipped, and vaccinated. Scooter's adoption fee is $200. If you are interested in adopting a CAWS pet, please fill out an online application at http://caws.org/adoption-application If you are interested in adopting a CAWS pet, please fill out an online application at https://caws.org/adoption-application

animal.description:
Noel was found on the side of a busy service road right around Christmas. Unable to see, she struggled finding her way out of the road. One of our long term supporters happened to find her and loaded her up to take care of her. While we initially thought that Noel was completely blind and had lost one eye, we have since detected some vision as well as a partially functioning eye behind a severely overgrown cyst. Unfortunately, Noel was initially diagnosed with cancer but she shows no sign of illness and we think it's a miracle! She LOVES LOVES LOVES every minute at TBC Animal Rescue and adores all of the staff and volunteers but she deserves a home! She likes to walk on the leash and she absolutely adores belly rubs. We would love for Noel to find an adopter of even a loving foster home where she could live out her life and receive the tender care she so deserves.
If you would like to adopt this sweet furbaby, please complete our pre-qualification application at this link: https://bit.ly/2CCVFPV

animal.description:
Meet Buddy, a seven year old Hound / Retriever / Shepherd mix. Buddy has been at the Rescue for a while now and even though we all love him to pieces - he really wants to find a loving furever home. Buddy enjoys nice walks and to cool off in one of our ponds. That's the way to make it through this Texas summer, he says. He loves to play tug with a rope toy, plays with a football, loves to walk on a leash and go in our woods to play. He is a great dog, and will be a terrific protector of his home and family. He is a playful boy with a medium amount of energy and gives sweet kisses too. Buddy has a slight food aggression. This can often be controlled with separate areas for feeding in a home but at the rescue we free feed so Buddy lives alone. Pls. come visit our lonely boy and give him some lovin'! This will be a great dog for a single girl that wants to feel protected and have a great companion and jogging buddy...
If you would like to adopt this sweet furbaby, please complete our pre-qualification application at this link: https://bit.ly/2CCVFPV

He is a staff favorite and loves to walk on the leash as well. He is affectionate once he gets to know you and loyalty is his nature. He was born around September of 2015.

animal.description:
Buddy Ray is about 12 years old now , and has gorgeous amber eyes and a very soft coat. 
 He has the Lab personality but a bit of the Chow fur. He is about 50 lbs. and full grown. He is shy at first, and fearful of a leash but will warm up when you give him a chance, and wants to be your friend. He is neutered and likely house trained... everyone tells us our dogs are housebroken because they are used to living outdoors, We have heard it so many times, we have come to believe it-especially when they are neutered at an early age like he was. 
Buddy Ray is one of those dogs that we think will blossom when you get him home, and is ready to be your great family dog! He gets along with the 2 girls he lives with, and is not rambunctious... but is playful.
If you would like to adopt this sweet furbaby, please complete our pre-qualification application at this link: https://bit.ly/2CCVFPV

animal.description:
Moon is a shy 1 year old old lab mix.

(Moon is required to go to a home with other dogs, this is where she finds her confidence)

 Her and her sister Shyne are looking for their forever homes! Moon and Shyne are 2 VERY SHY misunderstood pups who are looking for someone patient to help them learn it is ok to trust a human. 
Moon can be withdrawn and nervous at first, but it doesn't take long for her to break out of her shell. She loves other dogs, (of all sizes) and will tire them out with play. Moon also gets along with cats and kittens! 
Moon recognizes her name when called. She is not used to a leash but responds well to training. She is 90% housebroken, keep some pee pads available just in case. If you take her out upon walking, after meals, and before bed..she will ""hold"" it until she is outside. Her nerves can get to her when traveling, but she is starting to get the hang of the car rides! Squeaky toys and bones keep Moon busy when kenneled, and she is easy to kennel. 
At bedtime, Moon will gladly go inside her kennel and will sleep throughout the night. Mood does not bark a lot, she tends to be on the quite side. Moon is really a blank slate and there is a big world out there!! All she needs is an opportunity and a loving home to become your new BFF!! 

These sweet pups will NOT be available at our adoption event this coming Saturday at the Fort Collins Petco 2211 S. College Ave from 10am-1pm, but are available for one on one meet and greets throughout the week. If you are interested in these pups, please submit an application through our website aaanimalrescue.org. Please feel free to email with any questions allaboardanimalrescue@gmail.com.


Breed and size disclosure: As a rescue all of our dogs come to us from high-kill shelters or other rescues, so we do not get a lot of background or information on these dogs. We occasionally receive the mother with the puppies, but in most cases both parents are unknown. Because of this we do not know the full breeding of the dogs. We are required to list the dogs based on the breeds provided to us on their records, but they are all mixed breeds as far as we know, and we cannot guarantee the actual breeds of any of these dogs. Since the full breeding of the dogs is unknown we can also only give you an educated guess on the full-grown size of the dogs. All of the current information we have on the dogs is listed in their bio above. More information may be available at our adoption event, since a lot of the fosters turn in report cards on how the dog has done in their care when they drop them off. 

Adoption Process: If you are interested in adopting from us, the first step of our adoption process is to fill out an application online at http://aaanimalrescue.org/adoption_app.html. It takes us 24-48 hours to process your application and get back to you, via email. Applications turned in Friday afternoon or Saturday morning will not be processed since we are preparing for or at our adoption event. We do have applications on site at our events, but are not always able to approve them at that time and many of the dogs will already have holds on them, so we suggest you fill out an application prior to attending an adoption event. We can place a hold on one dog per approved applicant after a deposit fee has been received, please do not ask to hold a dog if you have not turned in an application and been approved, for the first hour of our adoption event, so that they can get the first chance to meet and hopefully adopt that dog. After the first hour of the event all dogs are available on a first come, first serve basis. If you already have an approved application on file, there will just be more paperwork and the adoption fee at the event, but you will be able to take home the dog/puppy that day. Since we are foster based and do not have a location, our dogs are only available to meet at our events, unless otherwise noted.

animal.description:
Isn't this girl a beauty? Ellie has been in training for the last few weeks and has been doing great with her obedience training! Ellie was one of the most neglected dogs we've ever taken in. She was emaciated, had almost no hair left and was in a tremendous amount of pain. After getting medical treatment, Ellie went to a foster with a male dog playmate. She loved her foster and became protective of the family. Who could blame her? When you've been treated as badly as she was, you would want to protect anyone who was being nice to you. 

Ellie has now learned her boundaries and when ""GSD protection mode"" is appropriate. Can you be the angel this girl wants and deserves? Ellie would love a home as an only dog, or with a large male who is laid back. She loves to play ball and go for walks. She needs to continue her socialization training and it's a requirement of her adoption that the new owner will participate in training sessions. Ellie will not be good for a home with small dogs or cats and due to her prey drive, we will not put her in a home with young children either. Ellie would be perfect for someone who has time to work on her training and who is experienced with German shepherds and their protection instincts. Ellie is house-trained and crate-trained.To apply for adoption, go to www.caninepetrescue.com and fill out our online adoption application. You will see answers to many of your questions in the introductory information.

animal.description:
Little Man is a 3 to 5-year-old pitbull mix he's been waiting a long time to find his family. In his kennel, this guy has lots of energy and can be quite vocal but is a very different dog ones outside kennel. He's happy to meet people when they stop by his kennel for a visit. He likes to go for walks and although initially he will pull only she does settle nicely once out walking. When hanging out in the yard he's quite independent and not a needy, all over you kind of dog. He'll stop by and check in with you, and then gets right back to exploring his environment. He was well behaved but wiggly during physical exam. He was not particularly food motivated nor did he respond to any commitments. Little Man does well with some dogs, but all times and definitely prefers females over males. He definitely prefers to be the one in charge; he would not do well with another dog trying to boss him around. Because he is dog selective, adult meet ahead of adoption would be a must. he is not a fan of cats, so a kitty free home is necessary. We think this guy would do well in the home with family looking for a dog with moderate energy and prepared to do some initial training. Because he has been in the shelter for so long, it's going to take a while for this guy to decompress and learn appropriate household behaviors. We think he's probably best suited to be in a home with children 10 years of age and older.

animal.description:
Please note that while we are closed to the public we will not be responding to pet inquiries. Once animals (especially puppies & kittens) are posted, we immediately begin receiving adoption applications. Adoption appointments are scheduled first come, first served. (See our adoption procedures below.)

Steele deserves a medal for being a volunteer and staff favorite! He loves playing in our dog parks but would rather have a home of his own with a yard. Steele needs daily exercise, so an active family would be a plus. Ask staff if you'd like to meet Steele outside in a dog park. He'll show you a good time! Steele's estimated DOB is 6/1/14. He weighs approximately 47 pounds and is done growing.

Steele was generously sponsored by Patty Snipes during our virtual Reigning Cats and Dogs event. Thank you Patty for sponsoring Steele!

HSPC's adoption fee is seventy-five-dollars through December 31, 2020, unless stated otherwise within the pet's description. At times, our adoption fees are lowered during special events that are posted to our website or Facebook page. Every pet that is available for adoption has been spayed/neutered, microchipped, and is up-to-date on vaccinations including heartworm preventative (canines). Adopters are required to schedule a wellness exam with their veterinarian at their cost within 7 days of adoption.

Please only submit one application. Once you are contacted by email, you will have an opportunity to provide us with any additional animal(s) under consideration.

We are currently closed to the public and will only be responding to pet inquiries accompanying an online adoption application. With one volunteer available to review all applications, we appreciate your patience as you wait for an email response. Adoption appointments are scheduled in the order that approved applications are received. You can find our adoption procedures and online application at warmhearts.org/adopt.

Justin is a beautiful boy that would love nothing more than to find his forever home. He came to the HSPC in 2015 after being found as a stray. Justin is a friendly dog who would make a great addition to any active family. He is smart and very trainable. He already knows how to sit, lay down and roll over and will pretty much do anything for treats! Justin is a strong active boy who will need a yard with a privacy fence where he will be able to get plenty of exercise. Please ask to meet Justin outside of his kennel. Justin's estimated DOB is 6/1/13; he weighs about 101 pounds.

Justin was generously sponsored by Phil Dively during our virtual Reigning Cats and Dogs event. Thank you Phil for sponsoring Justin!

animal.description:
Crystal is here with her sister ""Shay"" . They are a bonded pair and are looking for their forever home together.
Crystal and Shay talk a big game game but they are actually both sweethearts that need more time to bond than most.
Crystal loves to roll over on her back any time someone walks over to her , so that she is always prepared and ready for belly rubs! She is a chill, lap dog with a lot of love to give!
